<subSubSection pageId="171" pageNumber="172" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1437,1374,1545]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
This worldwide family of acalyptrate flies contains 85 predominantly Holarctic species (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[1152,1320,1410,1436]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refId="ref358584" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies. The natural history and diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books, Richmond Hill, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In his “ 
<emphasis box="[417,623,1446,1473]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Stirps Loncheinae</emphasis>
”, rather than in the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[943,1074,1446,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Piophilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Piophilidae</taxonomicName>
, proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart, P. - J. - M." box="[1238,1431,1446,1473]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refId="ref357717" refString="Macquart, P. - J. - M. (1835) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Dipteres. Tome deuxieme. N. E. Roret, Paris, 703 + 2 pp., 12 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14274" type="book" year="1835">Macquart (1835)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[151,340,1482,1509]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" pagination="243 - 274" refId="ref370928" refString="Rondani, C. (1875 a) Species italicae ordinis dipterorum (Muscaria Rndn.) collectae et observatae. Stirps XXII Lonchaeinae Rndn. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 6 (4) [1874], 243 - 274." type="journal article" year="1875">Rondani (1875a)</bibRefCitation>
described one Palaearctic species, considered as a junior synonym (
<bibRefCitation author="Zuska, J." box="[1104,1248,1482,1508]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refId="ref379151" refString="Zuska, J. (1984) Family Piophilidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Volume 9. Micropezidae - Agromyzidae. Elsevier Science Publishers, Amsterdam &amp; Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 234 - 239." type="book" year="1984">Zuska, 1984</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[1317,1365,1483,1509]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">type</typeStatus>
material is in the MZUF.
</paragraph>
